channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: How to Stay Sane When Markets Get Wild
Rocket Lab’s Archimedes engine test ‘a significant catalyst’ for new Neutron rocket, Cantor says
item.description: Rocket Lab reported a 71% second-quarter revenue hike after the market close Thursday. The company also said that it successfully fired its Archimedes engine for the first time. Rocket Lab shares are up 14.6% Friday.

item.title: A Couple Wants to Save More---for Retirement, College, Car and a House. But How?
item.description: A financial adviser has some suggestions on how the couple can get to where they want to go.

item.title: Oil prices snap streak of 4 straight losing weeks
item.description: Worries over the U.S. economic outlook eased and traders braced for potential retaliatory strikes by Iran and its proxies against Israel after the assassination of a top Hamas official in Tehran last week.

item.title: Crypto Fans Want a Bitcoin Reserve. Politicians Want Their Votes.
item.description: Donald Trump has said he wants to create a ‘strategic national bitcoin stockpile.’

item.title: Steak, dinner and more men: These have been keys to Sweetgreen’s recent growth
item.description: Sweetgreen’s stock soars as a key sales-growth metric reaches its highest level in two years and new initiatives pay off.

item.title: What Economic Dangers Is the Bond Market Pricing In?
item.description: Even more so than stocks, bonds are often seen as an economic bellwether.

item.title: Boeing bondholders get defensive ahead of potential downgrade to junk
item.description: Boeing’s bondholders have adopted a defensive trade in the last week of selling certain longer-dated notes and buying other, more recently issued bonds that will pay them more if the aerospace giant’s credit is downgraded.

item.title: Eli Lilly Is Gaining on Novo Nordisk in the Obesity Race
item.description: Despite a late start, the advantage is shifting toward the U.S. company.

item.title: Elizabeth Warren probes student-loan transfer that tanked borrowers’ credit scores
item.description: The letter to student-loan servicers and credit-reporting agencies is the latest example of scrutiny from the U.S. senator and consumer advocates.
